annotation.TEXT: Aha, made it!

Okay, let's actually fly here this time.
...Really?

If you don't hesitate, it's possible to avoid the Thwomps here entirely.
I'm going to assume every P block around here has a broom, since they have cement blocks above them.
0 attempts later...
Looks like this is another Bob-infested area.

Huzzah! Ten million points achieved!

I want to just move on to the next level now.

I guess I'll try to randomly kill unseeable things below.
Awesome.

11 attempts later...
SomeGuy712x's Yoshi asked me if the broom did anything to Chen, so let's find out...
Hey there everyone, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! Last time, I stomped a cat nine times. However, I'm not quite done torturing that feline yet...
I don't know if I'm supposed to kill those Thwomps below, but I'll do so anyway.
Pfft... Nice "hovering" there... However, I can still just barely make it. (On a couple of my failed runs, I actually did make it all the way across without losing my broom.)

Howard!
Aw, nuts... Wait, I can still make it!
Umm... I don't know if I'll want to check every pipe here... Well, if I don't have all of the stars after exploring the rest of the level, then I will.

Once again, taking an intentional hit just to take out a few more Thwomps!
Nailed a couple things (probably a couple of those Thwomps to the left). Alright, let's move on.

That's an obvious do-over.

And there's yet another President (Benjamin Harrison), who doesn't seem to have a middle name.
Yep. Okay, now to safely climb these spikes using drill stomps. Unlike Super Mario World, I can touch the non-pointy sides of the spikes safely.
Huh, somehow I was able to jump just before the dialogue appeared there.
As for the stars below the secret exit pipe... well, I'm hoping there's at least one broom around here. Okay, so here comes the area that I haven't explored yet.

Okay, let's destroy absolutely everything here!
Alright, let's properly bounce off of this guy this time.
Alright, let's resume killing guys, although it'll be harder to do with the broom.
Barf! Okay, get outta there! Retreat!
...Uhh... Apparently Theodore Roosevelt had no middle name, as far as I can tell. If I'm wrong, and he did have one, let me know.
Whoa, that is NOT a power up. Good thing I didn't hit that block earlier when I needed a power up.
Oh, looks like I've reached the end of the Bob gauntlet.
HARRY UP!
The flight wears off just before the B-switch counter ticks from 8 to 7, so be ready to start hovering then!
Yeah, all 4 remaining stars are up there!
Stephen!
Okay, he's done.

Okay, let's not rush forward and get Thwomped this time. Instead, let's use this miko suit to go on a rampage!

Now, as of this point, I still haven't actually seen what's further to the right of the secret exit pipe, so I'm still not going to check every pipe here yet.

Okay, the game gave me a broom, and it looks like I'll need it here, so that previous hit I took doesn't matter.
Pfft. Well, whatever.
Huzzah! And, now with this broom, I can just fly across this part!

Okay, let's not toss this FOE anywhere near that hole this time...
Hmm... No B-switch in sight. Maybe I'm supposed to bounce off of this duder to get across the spikes.
Aha! You can indeed smack Chen with the broom! And, it does the same damage as a stomp, so you'll need 9 hits either way to win.
Aw, nuts. SomeGuy712x's Yoshi also wanted me to go for the flawless victory, but that's not happening. Sorry, but I'm not going to bother trying again for that.
Good thing I didn't accidentally kill this white FOE. Oh, I hope I don't have to do babysitting again...

Just another duder.

Oh, but thanks to these potato chips, I still can!

Oh, come on... How did I let that hit me?
Well, there's the secret exit! And, I think this may very well be the final secret exit in the game!
There's another P block, likely another power up in case I screw up again.
Man, these guys would be easier to fight with a miko suit. (And, I realize now that there was one more miko suit to the left I could've gotten, above the B-switch bridge. Oops.)
To be continued... Ze!
Alan!
Okay, if I hover just right after my flight runs out...
Uhh... I think I did something wrong. I thought that was just another forced hit situation, but tanking didn't work. Also, I think those are the Thwomps I saw from above earlier.
And there's yet another forced hit situation.
Worth it! ...Maybe.
Well, there's a broom, so yep, I can get those stars up there now.
Whoa, I meant to land on the top block there, but whatever. Now for the next part, the best method seems to be to hit the B-switch and fly+hover UNDER the green bridge.

Stephen! (Grover is actually Cleveland's middle name, so I'm going with Stephen, his first name, here.)
Hmm... I think I should've maybe tried flying. Well, I'm just gonna start over again, since it's still early in the level.
At least there was a replacement power up right there. It's like the game expected me to screw up once. Let's try to avoid screwing up again if possible.
Umm... I think that block had another broom, which I squandered. Well, I'll just skip those stars below, since I died once and can't get a perfect on this run.
Sacrifice your miko suit to the spikes just before grabbing the broom, then enter the pipe during your mercy invincibility.
Oh, man! I think I can just keep going like this!
It seems like it's actually possible to avoid the forced hits in this level in most cases. (Although, the spikes right below the 2nd area's entrance do force an unavoidable hit.)
Okay, so maybe I fly without hitting the B-switch?
Alright, so up next will be another boss battle. Will I be able to outfox this boss? Find out next time!
